    {
      "section_title": "Recommendation for Achieving Calorie Restriction",
      "items": [
        {
          "item_title": "Calorie Restriction Recommendations",
          "keywords": ["calorie restriction", "restrictive diet", "moderate-intensity exercise", "weight loss maintenance"],
          "blocks": [
            {
              "block_heading": "Recommendations",
              "block_type": "list",
              "data": [
                "Adherence to restrictive diet (such as low-carbohydrate, low-fat, high-fiber) to create energy deficit through reduced food intake",
                "Moderate-intensity exercise is recommended for adults with obesity (Strong recommendation)",
                "More than 150 minutes/week is generally needed to show any weight loss",
                "Exercise may be even more helpful for maintenance than for induction of weight loss"
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "section_title": "Concept of Energy Balance & General Notes",
      "items": [
        {
          "item_title": "Energy Balance",
          "keywords": ["energy balance", "calorie intake", "calorie expenditure", "weight stability"],
          "blocks": [
            {
              "block_heading": "Principles",
              "block_type": "list",
              "data": [
                "Calories in = Calories out → Stable Body Weight",
                "Calories in > Calories out → Weight Gain",
                "Calories in < Calories out → Weight Loss"
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "item_title": "General Notes",
          "keywords": ["weight loss goals", "complex carbohydrates", "spot reduction", "sustainable lifestyle", "omega-3", "vitamins", "healthy fats", "extreme diets", "body composition", "fluid-only diets"],
          "blocks": [
            {
              "block_heading": "Notes",
              "block_type": "list",
              "data": [
                "For adults with overweight or obesity, achieving a weight loss of 5-10% of their body weight over 3-6 months is recommended for safe, sustainable results and significant health benefits",
                "Focus on eating complex carbohydrates such as whole grains, fruits, and vegetables, and reduce simple carbs such as sugar, white rice, and pastries",
                "Patient can't target fat loss to specific areas of body",
                "There is no magic pill or drink to lose weight. Focus on making sustainable lifestyle changes like healthy diet and regular exercise",
                "Omega-3 doesn't increase weight, it helps losing weight by stimulating metabolism",
                "Vitamins don't increase weight, they are important for cells to carry out their functions",
                "Healthy fats like fatty fish, nuts, and olive oil can help lower cholesterol levels and keep you feeling full",
                "Extreme diet will make you lose weight, but it can lead to deficiencies in essential vitamins and minerals and affect digestive health",
                "Stable weight might result from gaining muscle while losing fat, so it's important to assess body composition, not just the number on the scale",
                "Avoiding food and relying only on fluids is unhealthy and can lead to muscle loss, and weight gain in the future",
                "Omega-3 stimulates metabolism and aids weight loss (does not cause weight gain)",
                "Vitamins support cellular functions but do not contribute to weight gain"
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "section_title": "Patient Counseling on Diet",
      "items": [
        {
          "item_title": "Diet Counseling",
          "keywords": ["mediterranean diet", "low-carb diet", "calorie-restricted diet", "diet counseling"],
          "blocks": [
            {
              "block_heading": "Mediterranean Diet",
              "block_type": "text",
              "data": "High in healthy fats, low in processed foods"
            },
            {
              "block_heading": "Low-Carb Diets",
              "block_type": "text",
              "data": "May benefit insulin-resistant patients"
            },
            {
              "block_heading": "Calorie-Restricted Diets",
              "block_type": "text",
              "data": "Tailored to individual needs"
            },
            {
              "block_heading": "Dietary Diagram (Arabic)",
              "block_type": "list",
              "data": [
                "تناول الدهون الصحية (مثل زيت الزيتين الكانولا) عند طهي الطعام وتحضير السلطة، وعلى مادة الطعام، قلل من تناول الزيدة وتجنب الدهون المتحولة.",
                "كلماً زاد أكل الخضروات و تعددت اصنافها ذادت الفائدة البطاطا أو البطاطا المقليه لا تدخل ضمن الخضروات.",
                "تناول الكثير من الفواكه بألوانها المتنوعه.",
                "تناول الماء أو الشاي أو القهوة (مع قليل من السكر أو من دونه) قلل الحليب ومنتجات الألبان (إلى 2 – 1 حصة يومياً) وقلل العصائر (إلى كوب صغير يومياً)، تجنب المشروبات السكرية.",
                "تناول مجموعة متفرعة من الحبوب الكاملة (مثل خبر القيم الكامل والأوز الأسمر والمحكومة من الحبوب الكاملة) قلل من الحبوب المصفاة (مثل الأوز الأبيض والخبر الأبيض).",
                "تناول السمك والدجاج واليقول والمكسرات، قلل تناول اللحوم الحمراء الجبن وتجنب تناول شرائح اللحوم الباردة والانواع الأخرى المعالجة صناعياً."
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
